post_text:
Thank You to everyone who ordered & came to pick up Mobile Meals today!!! Not back for a first day, but we do realize there were a few issues! We DID figure it out once we got back to our office.... a printer issue meant that all the tickets didn't get printed properly... but we didn't realize it until it until we got back to our office. We sincerely apologize! And we fixed the problem, so it won't happen again! Thanks for hanging in there with us!

If you are virtual learning tomorrow, you can still order breakfast & lunch for tomorrow pick up at any one of our Mobile Meal sites! The cut off for ordering is 9pm the night before. And here's the best part: BREAKFAST & LUNCH are FREE for all students until December 31, 2020. If you do order... please either be sure to pick up... or let us know you are not picking up... so we can be prepared!

Since schools moved to distance learning in March, the teams in school cafeterias across the country did not stop or slow down. They pivoted and brought food to hungry kids in their communities. Same thing during the summer. And now that we are shouldering into the unknown once again for this upcoming academic year...they will continue to feed their kiddos. Lunch Lady is a cartoon hero, these people are REAL HEROES! #2020Challenge

post_text:
Happy 4th of July! This is the perfect weekend to celebrate with some delicious healthy recipes!

COVID19 Tip: If you are having some people in, or if you are taking food to a gathering, consider portioning out what you are bringing so that serving utensils are not being shared! Some ideas: Cupcakes vs Cake, Macaroni & Cheese baked in muffin cups line with papers vs baked or served in one large casserole, cute individual veggie cups vs. a veggie & dip platter. We'll post some ideas for you throughout the next 2 days.

And don't forget to wear a mask, especially if you cannot social distance! We want all of our friends to stay healthy & safe!!

post_text: Are you a #Dolewhip fan? We‚Äôve never tried the real thing, but this blended pineapple frozen treat was the perfect cool treat for a humid steamy day! We blended 2 cups of frozen pineapple (1 package) with about 1/3c whole milk Greek yogurt (use either plain or vanilla) and blend in a food processor or blender u til smooth & creamy. If it‚Äôs too thick, you can add a little pineapple juice or coconut milk to help it blend smoothly! We ate this straight out of the blender, topped with local #mainestrawberries , but we also put about 1/2 in the freezer for later! Super YUM and super refreshing!!

post_text:
RSU#14 Families: Important Summer Meals NEWS!

Due to an extension of USDA area/site eligibility waivers, we are able to offer Summer Meals in 2 sites this summer! We will be open Monday through Thursday at both Windham Middle School and Jordan Small Middle School for FREE summer meals (breakfast & lunch) for all children ages 18 years old and under.

There are a few things to note:
1. Meals will be served To Go, and must be picked up by a parent or guardian. Each day the meal pack will include lunch for the day of pick up, and breakfast for the following day.
2. You will be asked how many children you are picking up meals for.
3. On Thursday, the meal distribution will be bulk food, enough for multiple days, to carry you through the weekend.
4. These meals are being provided by Westbrook School Department, in a collaboration between RSU#14 and Westbrook School Department.
5. Pick Up Time at Windham Middle School will be 10:45-11:15. Pick Up at Jordan Small Middle School will be 11:15-11:45.

Honoring School Food Heroes
text:
During the past three months, US school food heroes worked tirelessly to nourish our children on the frontlines of COVID-19. They served millions of emergency meals while continuing to support local food producers. Please share this video and join Tom Colicchio TIPS for School Meals That Rock, Chef Ann Foundation, Lifetime Foundation, Wellness in the Schools and Whole Kids Foundation in thanking them for their endless passion and commitment to #FeedingOurFuture. Visit www.schoolfoodheroes.org to learn more.

YOUTUBE.COM
Honoring School Food Heroes

post_text:
We are excited to share this great news! Due to an extension of USDA area/site eligibility waivers, we are able to offer Summer Meals in 2 sites this summer! We will be open Monday through Thursday at both Windham Middle School and Jordan Small Middle School for FREE summer meals for all children ages 18 years old and under. There are a few things to note:
1. Meals will be served To Go, and must be picked up by a parent or guardian.
2. You will be asked how many children you are picking up meals for.
3. On Thursday, the meal distribution will be enough food for multiple days, to carry you through the weekend.
4. These meals are being provided by Westbrook School Department, in a collaboration between RSU#14 and Westbrook School Department.
5. Meal Pick Up times will be announced early next week.

We had extra whole grain flatbreads leftover from Tuesday‚Äôs Tacos. We are adding them to bags while supplies last. Wondering how to use them?

They are so versatile! You can make tacos or mini pizzas, cold or hot sandwiches or even toast them for cinnamon toast or add some herbs & cheese, toast & melt the cheese and cut them for cheesy breadsticks. The center ‚Äústars‚Äù are great toasted & brushed lightly with butter & cinnamon, or brushed with olive oil & herbs and toasted like croutons!

Enjoy!

Here is an update on our #Food4Kids Backpack Food Program. Tuesday June 9 will be our last day. We are open tomorrow, Friday, June 5 and Tuesday, June 9. We are preparing a resource sheet for families that will help you find summer meal sites or food pantries nearby. We will distribute this as soon as we have all the required information.

Under current USDA guidelines, our district does not qualify to operate a summer meals program when school is not in session, but we will be back in the fall, preparing healthy breakfasts & lunches for kids...

Please make sure you are "liking & following" our Facebook & Instagram pages so that you can have the most up to date information!

Thank you <3 to our community, our district AND our students & families for all the support during COVID-19.

post_text:
Cauliflower.... so delicious, crunchy & good for you! We have heard from some families that they just don't know what to do with the heads of cauliflower that we are sending home! One reason we send it home so often is that it is easy to pack (it is already wrapped) and it is a very versatile vegetable! It is delicious raw served with dip or hummus or roasted or made into buffalo cauliflower.

If you are struggling for ideas, we will post a few new cauliflower ideas - some of our favorite recipes - in the comment section!

post_text:
We want to wish all the moms & grandmothers a very Happy Mother‚Äôs Day! We know that this year will certainly be different as we practice social distancing on this holiday, when we usually want to gather & celebrate with our families. We hope that you are able to be celebrated and that you are able to connect with your loved ones, either within your homes with family you live with, or virtually or while practicing social distancing. We want to thank you, for entrusting us to feed your children on schools days, and we hope that in doing so, we make your day‚Äìto-day routine a little less chaotic! We miss the daily visits from the RSU#14 students, as they come through our cafeteria for breakfast & lunch‚Ä¶ and we cannot wait for the return of a more normal routine! We believe that students need adequate nutritious food‚Ä¶ whether they are learning in school, or at home, and it is our mission to make it possible.

#FeedingTheFuture #MothersDay #HappyMothersDay

We are passionate about feeding kids every single school day, whether we are physically in school & in classes or if we are in digital classrooms with e-learning. We believe that school meals are an essential part of the school day! Our team is amazing! And while we were not all together on #SchoolLunchHeroDay, we will certainly celebrate once we are all back together again!

This video is short - less than 2 minutes. Watch it & share it if you believe that #SchoolMeals are #FeedingTheFuture

Storing fresh #fruits and #veggies can be tricky because different produce requires different types of care. Especially during a time when we‚Äôre trying to reduce trips to the grocery store.

Since March 17, we have provided nearly 1200 #food4kids backpack food supply bags to families in our community! Each family receives a bags of fresh fruit & vegetables, a bag of milk, yogurt / cheese and a bag of shelf stable items like pasta, sauce, peanut butter, tuna and cereal! Sometimes, even muffins from our school bakery, bread & rolls! We love serving our community on this way, ensuring that our families have access to adequate food during this crisis. #somegoodnews #nokidhungry #FeedingAmerica #FeedingTheFuture

post_text:
If you've got too much milk taking up valuable space in your refrigerator.... Here are some great ways to use it up! Even if you or your child aren't "milk drinkers", there are some great ways to incorporate milk into you meals!
3 favorites in our household:

1. make oatmeal (or other hot cereal) in milk instead of water.
2. make hot cocoa with real milk instead of stirring a packet into hot water (even using a packet in warmed milk is a super creamy treat!)
3. steam milk to add to coffee or tea for a delicious latte!

DrinkMaineMilk.org Dayle Hayes Healthy Food Fuels Hungry Minds #healthyfoodfuelshungryminds

Dear RSU#14 families - We are committed to making sure that NO CHILD in RSU#14 goes hungry during our Covid-19 Closure. We believe that children should be well nourished every day of the week - whether there is school or no school.

Our district does not qualify for the Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) or the Seamless Summer Options (SSO) that you may have read about as you have been following the news updates about #Coronavirus & #Covid19.

In order to ensure that our students have access to healthy food and meals during this extended closure, our plan is to extend our #BackpackFoodProgram to any family. Please continue to monitor our Social Media sites as well as your email for more information. We will be sending out further information on Monday March 16 by the listserve. Updates will also appear on Facebook, Instagram (@lunch4kids_rsu14) and Twitter (@lunch4kidsRSU14)

post_text:
J is for jicama, and today we enjoyed crunchy, juicy jicama sticks all around the district as we eat our way through the alphabet for #NationalNutritionMonth!

Jicama is a delicous, crunchy vegetable sometimes referred to as yam bean, Mexican turnip, or Mexican potato. It is an edible root vegetable native to Mexico. In Central America, jicama is often sold by street vendors and commonly eaten raw, and seasoned with lemon or lime juice and chili powder.

It makes a great addition to salads & slaws, and is also good as an ingredient to soups & stews, maintaining a slightly crunchy texture!

#EatYourWayThroughTheAlphabet #HealthyFoodFuelsHungryMonds #FeedingtheFuture

TIPS for School Meals That Rock School Nutrition Services Dietetic Practice Group Healthy Food Fuels Hungry Minds

Today we are on the letter E as we eat our way through the alphabet for #NationalNutritionMonth! All schools will be serving our famous roasted edamame or our roasted edamame salad!

Edamame is the immature bean of the soybean pod. The are very high in potassium, and also a great source of vitamin c, iron & magnesium. It is an excellent source of plant based protein, so if you are trying to decrease your consumption of animal protein, adding edamame to your meal planning is a great idea! #EatYourWayThroughTheAlphabet #NNM2020 #healthyfoodfuelshungryminds

TIPS for School Meals That Rock Fruits & Veggies‚ÄîHave A Plant School Nutrition Services Dietetic Practice Group

post_text: Calling all elementary school kids! Please join us tomorrow, Friday February 28 for our Dolittle Fun Friday Breakfast! We are serving up creamy "Chunky Monkey" Smoothies and Dolittle "Donut" holes - which are whole grain & baked (never fried!) Milk, juice & fruit choices always are included with school breakfast, which is FREE for all students who qualify for free / reduced price meals and only $1.25 for all other students! A Fun Friday Breakfast is the perfect way to power up for the school day! We hope you will join us!

shared_text:
Jeanne Reilly‚ÄéTIPS for School Meals That Rock
February 25 at 2:14 PM ¬∑

Being involved on the admin level of TIPS for School Meals That Rock and the #Trayblazer initiative, I have been hesitant to nominate Trayblazers from my own district... but today I just couldn‚Äôt help myself ü§™. Windham Raymond School Nutrition Program‚Äôs High School team, led by the amazing kitchen manager Jackie Rallis , made these awesome chocolate-berry smoothies today, made with yogurt parfaits and chocolate milk that were leftover before our Winter Break! When we closed for break, they froze the leftover milk cartons & froze the leftover parfaits that would have otherwise be thrown away. This morning, they whipped them all up into a delicious parfait, served with a whole grain coffee cake muffin top! General Mills Convenience and Foodservice Dayle Hayes DrinkMaineMilk.org

post_text:
We served these #plantforward meatballs, recipe from USA Pulses at a small catering event yesterday and we received so many requests for the recipe, we have decided to scale the recipe down to family size! Scaled down, this recipe should make between 30-50 meatballs, depending on the size. We have sampled this recipe in the form of a meatball slider with students who raved about them, and gave the recipe a 1000 on a scale of 1-10! For our catering event, we also served them in marinara sauce for a meatball sub.
Scaled down recipe will be shared in the comments! TIPS for School Meals That Rock Dayle Hayes #HealthyFoodFuelsHungryMinds #Food4Change #ProteinChallenge

Did you know that we have a #WeekendBackpack Program that provides healthy, shelf stable, easy to prepare foods for kids over the weekend? We currently send over 150 bags of food home every weekend!

Want to donate to this great program? YOu can send a check to RSU#14 Weekend Backpack Program, or you can donate via Paypal using the link on our website. (link in the comments!)

shared_text:
Dayle Hayes checked in to Windham Raymond School Nutrition Program.
December 16, 2019 at 9:40 PM ¬∑ Windham, ME ¬∑

Last week in Windham Raymond School Nutrition Program, Jeanne Reilly and I tested a new recipe from USA Pulses: Rockin' Ranch Hummus ... which according to some students tasted like "Cool Ranch" chips. Introducing new foods takes promotion, signage and a delicious product. Based on our experience and the endorsement of a first grader who tried it with a whole grain chip, I can totally recommend this dip! Recipe information and link below in Comments. Becky Garrison

Dayle Hayes‚ÄéTIPS for School Meals That Rock
December 4, 2019 at 5:55 PM ¬∑

Perfect to SHARE within district and with community leaders: Impressive new infographic from Robert Wood Johnson Foundation "summarizing various research that has been published since nutrition standards for school meals were updated in 2012. One not to miss is that the Healthy Eating Index score (how well a meal follows Dietary Guidelines for Americans‚Äô recommendations) for greens/green beans category went from a score of 21/100 in 2009 to 72 in 2014! That is a remarkable change in just 5 years for the ~30 million kids who participate in school lunch daily." Thanks United Fresh Produce Association for sharing! Mollie Van Lieu Andrew Marshall

post_text: a great food safety tip as you prepare for your big dinner!
shared_text:
Eat Right Nutrition
November 20, 2019 at 5:45 PM ¬∑

Thinking about washing your Thanksgiving turkey? Think again!

A recent USDA study showed that 76% of participants did not even attempt to clean and sanitize their sink after washing or rinsing chicken. Of those who tried, 96% were not successful. Avoid the risk, don't rinse!

More information on what foods should (and shouldn't) be washed: https://sm.eatright.org/washfood

post_text:
If you involve kids in growing food, preparing & cooking food, they are more likely to eat the food!

Today, we made curried carrot soup & carrot muffins! Kids grew the carrots, peeled the carrots, chopped & grated the carrots, and cooked the soup and the muffins!

post_text:
#schoollunch means feeding the future whether you are in Maine or Pennsylvania... east coast to west coast! #schoolmeals are so important for the future of our nation, they are an investment in our infrastructure- the children of this country! This delicious lunch was our lunch today in Philadelphia. I was so fortunate to have the opportunity to visit one of their schools and eat lunch with the students grades 5-12! A highlight from #FNCE ! Philadelphia serves all school meals free to all students! What an amazing benefit for children in that city!

Such an amazing team of dedicated passionate school nutrition professionals! Thank you for letting us visit! #feedingthefuture #healthyfoodfuelshungryminds @schoolmealsthatrock

Time to mark your calendar! NEXT Thursday, October 17, we will be celebrating National Farm & School Month AND National Chili Month all on the same day! Our Maine Harvest Lunch menu includes:

*School Made Chili with local grass fed beef
* Shredded Pineland Farms Cheddar Cheese
*School Baked Cornbread
*crunchy Tortilla Chips: Montecito Roadhouse Tortilla Chips
*Roasted Root Vegetables from Mulberry Farms
*Tossed Salad made with locally grown greens
* Maine Apples

Be sure to join us!!! :-)
